{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox scientist | name = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Devendra_Lal.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date |df=yes|1929|02|14}} | birth_place = [[Varanasi]], India | death_date = {{death date and age |df=yes|2012|12|01 |1929|02|14}} | death_place = [[La Jolla]], [[California]], United States | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}--> | other_names = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = India | fields = Geophysics | workplaces = {{ublist |[[TIFR]] |Director, [[Physical Research Laboratory]] |[[Scripps Institution of Oceanography]] }} | patrons = | education = | alma_mater = {{ublist |[[Banares Hindu University]] |[[TIFR]] }} | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = 1960 | doctoral_advisor = <!--(or | doctoral_advisors = )--> | academic_advisors = Bernard Peters | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = {{ublist |[[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize for Science and Technology]], 1967 |[[Krishnan Medal]], [[Indian Geophysical Union]], 1965 |Fellow, [[Indian National Science Academy]], 1972 |Fellow, [[Royal Society|FRS]], 1979 |Fellow, [[Meteoritical Society]], 1970 |Foreign Associate, [[National Academy of Sciences]], 1975 |V.M. Goldschmidt Medal, [[Geochemical Society]], 1997 |[[Padma Shri]], 1971 }} | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = Aruna Lal (née Damany) | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> | footnotes = }}
'''Devendra Lal''' [[Fellow of the Royal Society|FRS]] (14 February 1929 – 1 December 2012) was an Indian [[geophysicist]].
==Life== He was born in [[Varanasi, India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scrippsnews.ucsd.edu/Releases/?releaseID=1314 |title=:: SCRIPPS OCEANOGRAPHY NEWS : : Obituary Notice: Devendra Lal: 1929-2012 :: |publisher=Scrippsnews.ucsd.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref> He graduated from [[Banaras Hindu University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sio.ucsd.edu/Profile/dlal |title=:: Scripps Institution Of Oceanography, Ucsd : ::: |publisher=Sio.ucsd.edu |date=2012-12-10 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref> He graduated from [[Bombay University]]; his thesis was on cosmic ray physics; his thesis adviser was [[Bernard Peters]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Devendra Lal (1929-2012) |publisher= Geochemical Society|url = http://www.geochemsoc.org/news/inmemoriam/devendra-lal-1929-2012/|website = www.geochemsoc.org|accessdate = 2015-09-10}}</ref>
He was Director, of the Physical Research Laboratory, Ahmedabad from 1972 to 1983.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiajournal.com/archives/32396 |title=Geophysicist Devendra Lal Dead |publisher=India Journal |date=2012-12-15 |accessdate=2013-05-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130629121336/http://www.indiajournal.com/archives/32396 |archivedate=29 June 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
He was Visiting Professor at Scripps Institution of Oceanography, [[University of California, San Diego]], from 1989 to 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://meteoriticalsociety.org/index.php?page_id=0&block_id=42&active_action=journal_view_main_detail&key=jowdjhjs9-42&post_id=59&comment_flag=1 |title=Devendra Lal, 1929-2012 |publisher=The Meteoritical Society |date=2012-10-21 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Special Correspondent |url=http://www.thehindu.com/sci-tech/science/geophysicist-devendra-lal-passes-away/article4178634.ece |title=Geophysicist Devendra Lal passes away |publisher=The Hindu |date=2012-12-08 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref> Devendra Lal was President of the [[International Union of Geodesy and Geophysics]] (IUGG) from 1983 to 1987.
