{{infobox Museum | name = National Museum of Natural History | image = National Museum of Natural History, Colombo.JPG | caption = Front view of National Museum of Natural History | map_type = Sri Lanka Colombo Greater | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = Location in greater Colombo | coordinates = {{coord|6|54|40.3|N|79|51|39.9|E|region:LK_type:landmark|display=inline, title}} | established = 1986 | founder = | location = [[Colombo]], [[Sri Lanka]] | director = | visitors = | type = Natural History | website = [http://www.museum.gov.lk/ Department of National Museums website] }}
The '''National Museum of Natural History''' is a museum that covers the natural heritage of [[Sri Lanka]]. The museum is located closer to the [[National Museum of Colombo]]. It was established on September 23, 1986 and became only one museum in Sri Lanka that represents [[natural history]] and [[natural heritage]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.museum.gov.lk/web/index.php?option=com_regionalm&task=regionalmuseum&id=11&Itemid=74&lang=en | title=National Museum of Natural History | publisher=Department of National Museums | accessdate=21 July 2015}}</ref>
The National Museum of Natural History exhibits rare and threatened with extinction such as natural heritage of plant and animal species [[endemic]] to Sri Lanka, over 5,000 specimens of mammals, [[jurassic]] period indigenous fossils and various kinds of [[Rock (geology)|geological rocks]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2008/05/18/spe02.asp | title=Our proud heritage | publisher=The Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka) | accessdate=21 July 2015}}</ref>
== Opening hours == The museum is open from 8.30 AM to 5.00 PM and close on public holidays.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.gic.gov.lk/gic/index.php?option=com_info&id=1716&task=info&lang=en | title=Museum Visit | publisher=Information and Communication Technology Agency of Sri Lanka | accessdate=21 July 2015}}</ref>
